[[File:Ariana beer.BG.1.JPG|right|thumb|200px|Ariana - [[lager]] and [[bock]], 2010s bottles]]
'''Ariana''' is a [[Bulgaria]]n beer brand, produced by the [[Zagorka Brewery]] since 2004. The company was established in 1884, and for most of its history brewed at the [[Ariana Brewery]] in central [[Sofia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ratebeer.com/beer/ariana/11948/|title=RateBeer|website=www.ratebeer.com|language=en|access-date=2018-05-14}}</ref> It was bought by [[Heineken]] in 1997 and currently{{when|date=May 2018}} has four brands – Ariana Light (5% ABV), Ariana Dark (5.5% ABV) and two citrus-flavoured brands available only in summer – Ariana [[Radler]] lemon and grapefruit (1.8% ABV).

