{{Unreferenced|article|date=July 2010}}

'''''At the Back of the Black Man's Mind''''' is a book by [[R.E. Dennett|Richard Edward Dennett]] published in 1906.  It provides many details on the [[folklore]], culture, and religion of the [[Bantu peoples|Bantu]] and [[Yoruba people|Yoruba]].  However, many of its characterizations would today be considered [[colonialism|colonialist]] or [[racism|racist]].  Also, it provides many theories about the facts presented which are incorrect or irrelevant.

