'''''Fuji House of Commotion''''' is a Nigerian [[sitcom]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/movies/throwbackthursday-how-well-do-you-remember-the-classic-fuji-house-of-commotion-sitcom-id4111099.html|title=#ThrowbackThursday: How well do you remember the classic "Fuji House of Commotion" sitcom?|last=Izuzu|first=Chidumga|access-date=2018-08-16|language=en-US}}</ref> It was produced and directed by [[Amaka Igwe]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailytrust.com.ng/iconic-director-amaka-igwe-dies.html|title=Iconic Director Amaka Igwe Dies|author=Adie Vanessa Offiong|date=Apr 29, 2014|website=dailytrust.com.ng|publisher=Daily Trust|access-date=Sep 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pmnewsnigeria.com/2014/04/29/fuji-house-of-commotion-producer-amaka-igwe-is-dead/|title=Fuji House of Commotion producer Amaka Igwe is dead - PM NEWS Nigeria|date=2014-04-29|work=PM NEWS Nigeria|access-date=2018-08-16|language=en-US}}</ref>

It stars Kunle Bamtefa as Chief Fuji, Toun Oni as Mama Moji,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2010/07/good-night-mama-t/|title=Good Night, Mama T... - Vanguard News|date=2010-07-14|work=Vanguard News|access-date=2018-08-16|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pmnewsnigeria.com/2010/07/08/actress-toun-oni-is-dead/|title=Actress, Toun Oni Is Dead - PM NEWS Nigeria|date=2010-07-08|work=PM NEWS Nigeria|access-date=2018-08-16|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Ngozi Nwosu]] as Peace,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2013/07/ngozi-nwosu-returns-to-fuji-house-of-commotion/|title=Ngozi Nwosu returns to Fuji House of Commotion - Vanguard News|date=2013-07-09|work=Vanguard News|access-date=2018-08-16|language=en-US}}</ref> Louisa Onu as Ireti, [[Iretiola Doyle|Ireti Doyle]] as Caro,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2015/06/i-took-my-3-month-old-baby-to-the-set-of-fuji-house-of-commotion-iretiola-doyle/|title=I took my 3-month old baby to the set of Fuji House of Commotion -Iretiola Doyle - Vanguard News|date=2015-06-13|work=Vanguard News|access-date=2018-08-16|language=en-US}}</ref> Jude Orhoha as Gbenro, John Njamah as Rabiu, and  Chika Chukwu as Jumoke among others.

The sitcom revolves around a rich man (Chief T.A. Fuji) who is married to four women and had numerous kids to provide for.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/movies/throwbackthursday-how-well-do-you-remember-the-classic-fuji-house-of-commotion-sitcom-id4111099.html|title=#ThrowbackThursday: How well do you remember the classic "Fuji House of Commotion" sitcom?|last=Izuzu|first=Chidumga|access-date=2018-08-16|language=en-US}}</ref> Some episodes also feature family friends such as Victor Eze as Alika.

