{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians --> | name = Liis Lemsalu | image = Liis Lemsalu 20120706b by Ahsoous.jpg | caption = | image_size = 230px | background = solo_singer | birth_name = | alias = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1992|10|20|df=y}} | death_date = | birth_place = [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]] | instrument = | genre = {{Hlist|[[pop music|Pop]]|[[soul music|soul]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]}} | occupation = Singer | years_active = 2011–present | label = [[Universal Music Group]] | associated_acts = | website = | current_members = | past_members = }}
'''Liis Lemsalu''' (born October 20, 1992 <ref>{{cite news|url=http://publik.delfi.ee/news/superstaar/liis-lemsalu.d?id=43840633 |title=Liis Lemsalu |publisher=Publik.ee|accessdate=17 June 2011 |language=Estonian}}</ref> in [[Pärnu]], [[Estonia]]) is an Estonian singer.
Lemsalu rose to fame as the winner of the [[Eesti otsib superstaari (season 4)|fourth season of ''Eesti otsib superstaari'']], the Estonian version of [[Idol series]]. After winning, Liis went on tour with other participants of ''Eesti otsib superstaari'' and released a single ''"Kõnnime seda teed"'' together with the runner-up of the show, Artjom Savitski.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://publik.delfi.ee/news/superstaar/liisil-ja-artjomil-ilmus-tana-duett-konnime-seda-teed.d?id=47863279|title=Liisil ja Artjomil ilmus täna duett "Kõnnime seda teed"|accessdate=17 June 2011|publisher=Publik.ee|language=Estonian}}</ref> She was then signed to [[Universal Music Group]]. She has featured in Eesti Laul, Estonia's selection for the Eurovision Song Contest four times, missing out on the final twice and qualifying twice. Her best entry, Made Up My Mind, came 5th out of 10 in 2012. She has released successful songs of which many have over 100k views on streaming service YouTube. Her most popular song on the site "Sinu Ees" (''"In Front Of You"'' in English) had 2.1 million views as of 2017 which is double the population of her home country, Estonia.
==Songs performed in ''Eesti otsib superstaari''== {|class="wikitable" !Week !Title !Original Artist !Result |- !colspan="4"|Semi-finals |- |[[Eesti otsib superstaari (season 4)#First week|Semi-final: Week 1]] || "Vanaisa kiri" || Indigolapsed ||style="background:#FBF373" | Jury Wildcard |- ||[[Eesti otsib superstaari (season 4)#Third week|Semi-final: Week 3]] || "[[At Last]]" || [[Etta James]] ||style="background: lightgreen" | Qualified to the Finals |- !colspan="4"|Finals |- |[[Eesti otsib superstaari (season 4)#Week 1|Week 1]] || "[[I Have Nothing]]" || [[Whitney Houston]] ||style="background: lightgreen" | Safe |- |[[Eesti otsib superstaari (season 4)#Week 2|Week 2]] || "15 magamata ööd" || [[Eda-Ines Etti]] ||style="background: lightgreen" | Safe |- |[[Eesti otsib superstaari (season 4)#Week 3|Week 3]] || "[[I Wanna Dance with Somebody (Who Loves Me)]]" || [[Whitney Houston]] ||style="background: lightgreen" | Safe |- |[[Eesti otsib superstaari (season 4)#Week 4|Week 4]] || "[[Proud Mary]]" || [[Tina Turner]] ||style="background: #E0F0FF" | Bottom three |- |[[Eesti otsib superstaari (season 4)#Week 5|Week 5]] || "[[L-O-V-E]]" || [[Nat King Cole]] ||style="background: #E0F0FF" | Bottom three |- |rowspan="2"|[[Eesti otsib superstaari (season 4)#Week 6|Week 6]] || "[[Smells Like Teen Spirit]]" || [[Nirvana (band)|Nirvana]] ||style="background: lightgreen" rowspan="2"| Safe |- | "Sajab lund" || [[Maarja-Liis Ilus]] |- |rowspan="2"| [[Eesti otsib superstaari (season 4)#Week 7|Week 7]] ||"Üle tumeda vee" || [[Smilers]]||style="background: lightgreen" rowspan="2"| Safe |- | "Den fyrste song eg høyra fekk" || [[:no:Per Sivle|Per Sivle]] |- |rowspan="2"| [[Eesti otsib superstaari (season 4)#Week 8|Week 8]] ||"[[Messiah (Handel)|Messiah]]" || [[George Frideric Handel]]||style="background: lightgreen" rowspan="2"| Safe |- | "[[Someone Like You (Adele song)|Someone Like You]]" || [[Adele]] |- |rowspan="3"| [[Eesti otsib superstaari (season 4)#Super-final|Finale]] || "At Last" || Etta James ||style="background: lime" rowspan="3"| '''Victory''' |- | "Mis maa see on?" || Siiri Sisask |- | "[[Crazy in Love (Beyoncé Knowles song)|Crazy in Love]]" || [[Beyoncé]] |}
==Discography==
===Album=== * ''Liis Lemsalu'' (2011) * ''RULES'' (EP) (26 november 2015) * ''+1'' (30 November 2017)
===Singles=== * "Kõnnime seda teed" (15 June 2011; together with Artjom Savitski) * "Shining Star" (22 September 2011) * "Wanna Get Down" (3 November 2011) * "Täitugu soovid" (28 November 2011) * "Made Up My Mind" ([[Estonia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2012|Eesti Laul 2012]] finalist, 5 out of 10 with 12 points) * "Lighting in the Bottle" (13 September 2012) * "Uhhuu" ([[Estonia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2013|Eesti Laul 2013]] semi-finalist, 9 out of 10 with 10 points) * "Rohkem värve" / "Got To Be" (English version) (2 September 2013) * "Sulle võin kindel olla" (3 October 2013) * "That Kinda" (5 May 2014) * "Slowly Dying" (4 November 2014) * "Hold On featuring Egert Milder" (Eesti Laul 2015 semi-finalist 7 out of 10 with 9 points) * "Fire" (25 May 2015) * "Breaking the Rules" (12 November 2015) * "Sinu ees" ("In Front of You" in English) (31 May 2016) * "Keep Running" / "Aeg on Käes" (Estonian version) (Eesti Laul 2017 Finalist, 7 out of 10 with 10 points) * "Sinuga koos" ("Next to You" in English) (29 March 2017)
==Personal life== Lemsalu studied at the Tallinn Nõmme Gymnasium. She is a daughter of a former professional football player [[Marek Lemsalu]].
