The '''MR8 road''' is a major highway of [[Swaziland]]. Along with the [[MR3 road|MR3]] and [[MR7 road]]s it is considered to form the "backbone of Swaziland's internal transport system."<ref name="Federation1993">{{cite book|author=International Road Federation|title=World highways|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OmBUAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=22 March 2012|date=1 January 1993|publisher=Route One Publishing}}</ref> It connects the MR3 road east of [[Manzini, Swaziland|Manzini]] at {{coord|26|29|16|S|31|27|17|E|}} with [[Lavumisa]]/[[Golela]] at {{coord|27|19|4|S|31|53|18|E|}}. It passes through the [[Mkhaya Game Reserve]].

