{{Politics of Burundi}}

The '''Rally for the People of Burundi''' ({{lang-fr|Rassemblement du peuple Burundais}}) is a [[political party]] in [[Burundi]]. It was headed by [[Ernest Kabushemeye]], until his assassination in 1995, since when [[Balthazar Bigirimana]] has been party leader.

==History==
The RPB was registered on 12 August 1992.<ref>[http://www.afrique-express.com/afrique/burundi/burundi-partis-politiques.html Les principaux partis politiques du Burundi] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819120753/http://www.afrique-express.com/afrique/burundi/burundi-partis-politiques.html |date=2014-08-19 }} Afrique Express</ref> It supported victorious candidate [[Melchior Ndadaye]] of the [[Front for Democracy in Burundi]] in the [[Burundian presidential election, 1993|1993 presidential elections]].<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/bi.html Elections in Burundi] African Elections Database</ref> In the [[Burundian legislative election, 1993|1993 parliamentary elections]] it received 1.7% of the vote, failing to win a seat.<ref>[http://www.content.eisa.org.za/old-page/burundi-1993-national-assembly-election-results Burundi: 1993 National Assembly election results] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150704081523/http://www.content.eisa.org.za/old-page/burundi-1993-national-assembly-election-results |date=2015-07-04 }} EISA</ref>

